reviewText: low quality copy of a VHS copy from a 16mm positive of a 1930 production of a sound comedy with some intertitles introducing changes of locations.
picture obviously unable to be restored. Sound quality bad. Whole movie too blurry to enjoy. Ironically the most expensive of its type that I have purchased
Any movie that Jeanette MacDonald is in is worth watching. This is a comedy from 1930 and it is funny. Jeanette MacDonald was beautiful and incredibly talented. Highly recommend this movie!
A very good, exceptional  value for a rarely seen movie with Jeanette MacDonald before she was teamed with Nelson Eddy.
